Here is it, my first fight yard map, Dark Reactor.

It's a dark map with corourful and intense hdr lighting, The transitions between the colours are really smooth and just beautiful. :)

The gameplay is skill oriented and really really fast. The enemy comes here from everywhere. There are no sidepaths, all paths in this map make sense and you will use the complete map. At first i create more corridors and test air vents, but more just reduce the speed and a great fy map should be fast as possible.

All textures in the map are made by me and the big part is in 2048x2048, just the skytexture is not my work. But the hdr version is my work :) I'm very proud of the textures, detailed, smooth and so big. Here is the the 8K preview, to show what i mean.

The map is extreme vis optimized. That improves the fps in important areas up to 100%. Performence is here not a problem.  The map have a 3 times higher min framerate than aim_bridgecut.  It runs on a i7 @ 4400mhz with 220fps min, but only at the end of the map( weapon automat's), the most time 300 frames, on aim_bridgecut i have 70fps min and 100 frames at spawn.

The Soundtrack for the video and the loops in the map are made by True (The real unique entertainment). He works with me on a complete soundtrack "Dark Symphonie" for my overloaded project. 6 tracks are done, maybe it come 1 or 2 more on this sampler.

Here is the gameplay trailer of fy_dark_reactor, and the first soundtrack by true from "Dark Symphonie" that calls "Timeline". Really dark, atmospheric and really great produced.



You have a share-online or uploaded premium account?
So, please use one of the alternate links. :)

This map is just a warmup for me, the next big thing comes in 3 or 4 weeks with a remastered version of my map de_newprodigy. Again with a lot new textures. I work also on a cs_italy remaster with new textures, lighting and details. But I'm more focused on my own maps, so I can't say how much time this need. It's planned to remaster all official maps of source. Oh man, that's really much work for me. :)

Feedback and critics are welcome, but please nothing about the filesize, I know it's crazy (635mb!), but it needs what it needs. p.s. the textures are all compressed, just the normals are uncompressed.

Ok, I must say it: Please rate it! That was hundreds of hours for me, to rate needs just some seconds :D



Update: I fixed a bug, that i've found on the automats.
And I reduce the mapsize a little bit (617mb).

Next map: de_new_prodigy

This is my first map uploaded to FPSB...

This map is a maze-like tunnel underneath a flat surface. There are 4 points which lead up to the surface, these points are where teams will spawn, so the team has a choice of going up to the surface to fight or staying underneath in the darkness to prey on their victims. I would reccommend using a flshlight... There is also a small pool of water in the middle of the map so listen out for sloshing footsteps in water...

Since this is not the final release, I would like to ask you a couple of Questions...
-Should the tunnels be light or dark?
-What sort of props/obstacles should I add to the surface?

Please be nice when giving feedback since this is the first map I have uploaded, and is DEFINITELY not the final version-the reason I uploaded was mostly to get feedback.

*********************************** 
A Counter-strike source map
*********************************** 
TITLE: fy_cubicles
AUTHOR: Tropical_Plague
FILENAME: fy_cubicles.bsp / fy_cubicles.res / wgc.vmt / wgc.vtf
FILESIZE: 3.98mb
DATE RELEASED: 2 May 2011

INSTALLATION INSTRUCTIONS: Please put fy_cubicles.bsp and fy_cubicles.res in \cstrike\maps. 

Put the \fy_cubicles folder, which contains wgc.vmt and wgc.vtf, in the \cstrike\materials folder. Without these, the custom graphic in the map will appear with the pink and black checkerboard replacement texture.

DESCRIPTION: fy_cubicles is a counter-strike source fight yard map set in a high-rise office building. It contains pickup weapons as well as buy zones and a single bombsite on the roof.

BUGS: None. 

COMMENTS: I originally made this map for FarCry in 2004. It was a popular deathmatch map. I then remade it for Crysis in 2007, and then for FarCry2 in 2009. It has had over 30,000 downloads for Farcry2. Although the unusual design and gameplay are not everyone's cup of tea, a lot of people enjoy it. So when I decided to start learning the Hammer editor and to make my first CSS map, I stuck with the tradition. This version contains elements of all the three previous "Cubies" maps, plus I went with the orange dev texture for the desks and dividers to give it that CSS feeling.
This is my first map, have fun. This is a dark map for fast action. Makes flashlight useful.

Fy_ctf_iceworldz

By ZaLoS

Custom textures by ZaLoS, IceCreamLock


CTF!!!

Each team has a flag, the first to take the other teams flag and return it to their base, while their own flag is in their base, wins!

Losers BURN.

(Specifically: The losing team will catch on fire and burn for 15secs then get hit by 1k damage)


How it works:

To pick up the flag you need to drop your pistol and pick up the pistol the flag is attached to. 

To score, carry your flag back to your base and drop it near your flag, if your flag is not there you can not score.


NOTE: This map is not intended for DeathMatch servers. This map will not crash a deathmatch server however the CTF portion of gameplay will not work properly. This is caused by the DM mod destroying guns after people die. This also destroys the flag when people die, or try to score a point.

The Kosher Pork for seting up the beta and to all the beta testers! Additional thanks to fpsbanana.com, www.solidsurf.info
